title: Phancies phænix. Or. The peerless paragon of the times Being a young gallants description of a lady which he hath settled his thoughts on, [illegible] never to change, not to love any other beauty of face in the world. And is perswaded if there be a phœnix in the world, 'tis she. To an amorous new tune.
